metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #470
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.description:

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. metadata.name: Shift #216
metadata.description:
A generative algorithm honing the power of vertical displacement.

How simple may a generative algorithm be while simultaneously staying diverse enough for each art piece to be truly unique? Shift is the result of an exploration into this space, basing its existence on two principles — dissection and vertical shifting. Each variable in this art engine has been meticulously weighted, giving rise to high diversity and the possibility of epic combinations. 

Shift is a series of 888 unique pieces.

############

Display resolution is 1000x1400. Press ’s’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x8400 hi-res image. This may take a while to generate depending on your hardware.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022

metadata.name: Scythe #63
metadata.description: The title is chosen for the tool's purpose, to harvest. Remove what has already flourished and allow for new growth. This sets my intent to continue exploring my art through creative coding and generative art. The work uses the beauty of Bezier's curves alongside deep textures and rich colours. I wanted this work to stay grounded in my design background but as I wrote the code it allowed me to discover new ways of creating. I hope you the viewer, finds a connection with Scythe.

metadata.name: Vast Difference #27
metadata.description:
This piece explores the dynamic creation of vascular cages around generative geometries. Particles are projected at a generative form, stopping when contact is made with any of the form's faces. A curve is then generated through the particles, based on the order of particle-face collision. Finally, custom tube geometry is extruded along the curve path, determining the final cage mesh. 

Interactivity: 
Panning, rotating, zooming and toggling both the internal form and particle nodes on/off.

Mouse/Trackpad:
drag -> camera rotation
drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
o, n: hide | show particle nodes
i, v: hide | show internal form
p: screen capture

Notes:
Some renders produce noticeable delays, including possible browser alerts/warnings. This is expected behavior.
Please post your favorite 'Vast Difference' screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Imoogi #168
metadata.description:
A hornless ocean dragon, sometimes equated with a sea serpent. Imoogi literally means, "Great Lizard". The legend of the Imoogi says that the sun god gave the Imoogi their power through a human girl, which would be transformed into the Imoogi on her 17th birthday. Legend also said that a dragon-shaped mark would be found on the shoulder of the girl, revealing that she was the Imoogi in human form.

metadata.name: street tales #2 #85
metadata.description:
130 random images in 6 layers

photos by me at important moments of hip-hop scene in brazilian northeast

1 - day of recording the music video 999 of rapper “Baco Exu do Blues”, where the first live music of "Sulicidio" happened (historical diss against the musical system, that centralizes the attentions in a single region of the country)

2 - day of recording the music video “Dexunego” of rapper “Diomedes Chinaski”, in streets of Recife and first time opening a show for the legends RACIONAIS MC's (most important hip-hop group in Brazil)

3 - day of recording the music video “Dama de Copas” of rappers “Mobb” and “Morris”

4 - images from the street event "Laminha", award for the best underground/illegal taggers(pixadores) from Salvador-Bahia

5 - images from underground event "Vapor" in downtown of Recife-Pernambuco

o underground vive !
